(followups to alt.security.pgp)

Jerry Schwartz (jerrys@truevision.com) wrote:
: seems that pgp isn't as secure as I would like it to be on unix.
: By this I mean that by setting a public/secret key pair anyone that
: is logged in as me, someone being root then doing a su to my login, can
: decrypt my files because of access to my secring.pgp file.

Your assumption would be correct if the secring.pgp file were
not encrypted with IDEA and your secret passphrase.

But you are correct that you aren't really very secure on
multi-user machines in the first place since opponents can
monitor your keyboard streams and pipes, etc.


